{
  "texts": [
    "This reassures us about the reliability of AI in ophthalmology, reducing the burden on human graders and facilitating early intervention, instilling a sense of confidence in the capabilities of AI.",
    "In addition to the binary classification of referable DR, AI models have been developed to grade the severity of DR and identify specific pathological features such as microaneurysms, hemorrhages, and exudates.",
    "Gulshan et al.",
    "extended their previous work by training a CNN to classify DR severity into five levels, achieving a quadratic weighted kappa of 0.84, indicating substantial agreement with human graders (11).",
    "Quellec et al."
  ]
}